sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TrrnB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Akash Bhattacharjee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from James Chappell's paper (Nature Chemical Biology, 2015), from the STAR reporter construct.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Was syntheszed as a block along with j23119, STAR-target, SFGFP.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SF-GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Akash Bhattacharjee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is taken from the construct as used by James Chapelle, for the STAR reporter plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This was synthesised as a block with j23119, STAR target.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the scar sequence of the BBb1 assembly scheme. For more information, refer to [http://openwetware.org/wiki/Template:AndersonLab:BBb_Standard BBb Standard Description Page].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bing Xia

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Akash Bhattacharjee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Same sequence that was used by James Chappell (Nature Chemical Biology, 2015) in designing the STAR reporter plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Was synthesized as a block with j23119, STAR-target, SFGFP, TrrnB

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: STAR targe
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: When transcribed, it produces the sense RNA which is also complementary to the STAR-antisense RNA. In the absence of STAR, it forms a hairpin structure and and prevent transcription of the downstream coding sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Akash Bhattacharjee
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This comes from the pAD1 attenuator sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This was synthesised as a composite sequence including the j23119 promoter, SFGFP and TrrnB terminator.
